1) Open Docker download page

Download:
https://docs.docker.com/docker-for-windows/install

2) Download and install Docker Desktop

Download the latest version from the above link and run the installer.

3) Open terminal to run Docker
powershell
Notes
4) System requirements

Docker Desktop works on:

Windows 10/11 Pro (64-bit)
Windows Server 2016 or later
Docker Basics
5) Docker Image

A Docker image is a package containing binaries and libraries required for an application.

6) Docker Container
A running instance of an image
Multiple containers can be created from one image
7) Docker Client
Interface to run Docker commands
Example:
docker ps
8) Docker Daemon

Background service that processes Docker commands.

9) Docker Registry

Online storage for Docker images.

10) Public Registry

Download images:

docker pull nginx
11) Private Registry

Used by organizations (no direct command — requires authentication).

12) Docker Host

Machine where Docker is installed and containers run.
